From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: mac80211: drop frames queued to a stopping interface in the AP encap path

ieee80211_8023_xmit_ap() parks frames on local->pending when the
queues are stopped. A frame that lands there after ieee80211_do_stop()
has flushed the pending queues for its interface is only released by
the plain skb purge in ieee80211_free_hw(), so a status-requested
frame (e.g. an EAPOL sent by hostapd while the interface goes down)
leaks its ack status entry and triggers the "Have pending ack frames!"
warning on teardown. Free frames for no-longer-running interfaces
through ieee80211_free_txskb() instead of queueing them.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>

--- a/net/mac80211/tx.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/tx.c
@@ -4838,6 +4838,16 @@ void ieee80211_8023_xmit_ap(struct ieee8
 	spin_lock_irqsave(&local->queue_stop_reason_lock, flags);
 
 	if (local->queue_stop_reasons[q] || !skb_queue_empty(&local->pending[q])) {
+		/* A frame queued here after ieee80211_do_stop() flushed the
+		 * pending queues for this interface is never freed through
+		 * mac80211 again and would leak its ack status entry ("Have
+		 * pending ack frames!" on hw free), so drop it properly.
+		 */
+		if (unlikely(!test_bit(SDATA_STATE_RUNNING, &sdata->state))) {
+			spin_unlock_irqrestore(&local->queue_stop_reason_lock, flags);
+			ieee80211_free_txskb(&local->hw, skb);
+			return;
+		}
 		skb_queue_tail(&local->pending[q], skb);
 		spin_unlock_irqrestore(&local->queue_stop_reason_lock, flags);
 		return;
